import React from 'react';
import {
    Grid,
    Typography,
    Card,
    CardContent,
    CardMedia
} from "@material-ui/core";

const ProjectList = () => {
    return (
        <Grid container justify="center" alignItems="center">
           <Card>
                <CardMedia />
                <CardContent>
                    <Typography gutterBottom variant="h5" component="h2">
                        WCLN LTI Provider solution
                    </Typography>
                    <Typography variant="body2" color="textSecondary" component="p">
                        I built a custom LTI provider solution for Western Canadian Learning Network to distribute
                        course content to school districts throughout Western Canada. It handles millions of resource
                        requests every year.
                    </Typography>
                </CardContent>
            </Card> 

            <Card>
                <CardMedia />
                <CardContent>
                    <Typography gutterBottom variant="h5" component="h2">
                        WCLN LTI Provider solution
                    </Typography>
                    <Typography variant="body2" color="textSecondary" component="p">
                        I built a custom LTI provider solution for Western Canadian Learning Network to distribute
                        course content to school districts throughout Western Canada. It handles millions of resource
                        requests every year.
                    </Typography>
                </CardContent>
            </Card> 
        </Grid>
    );
}

export default ProjectList;
